{
  "texts": [
    "The co-occurrence analysis of author keywords in the field of AI-assisted language learning and applied linguistics has yielded intriguing insights.",
    "The analysis of the three periods (as Figure E suggests) reveals an evolution in the field, with different topics and themes emerging in each period.",
    "In the first period (purple), spanning from 2016 to 2018, the focus was on ITS and ML, indicating the nascent stages of the use of AI in language teaching and learning.",
    "Robotics and intelligent CALL were also prominent areas of exploration during this period (Khalifa et al., 2019), suggesting an interest in leveraging technology to augment language learning and teaching.",
    "The study of lexical sophistication and learner corpus was also of interest, reflecting researchers' desire to develop AI-based tools for enhancing learners' lexical and grammatical proficiency."
  ]
}